statements: SELECT * FROM BirdMigrationLocations;
SELECT bird_name, location_lat, location_long FROM BirdMigrationLocations;
SELECT * FROM BirdMigrationLocations WHERE bird_name = 'Sparrow';
SELECT * FROM BirdMigrationLocations ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT bird_name, location_lat, location_long FROM BirdMigrationLocations WHERE location_long < 0;
SELECT * FROM BirdMigrationLocations ORDER BY bird_name DESC, timestamp ASC LIMIT 10
SELECT bird_name, location_lat, location_long FROM BirdMigrationLocations WHERE location_lat > 0 AND location_long < 0
SELECT bird_name, COUNT(*) FROM BirdMigrationLocations GROUP BY bird_name HAVING COUNT(*) > 1 ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
SELECT DISTINCT bird_name FROM BirdMigrationLocations ORDER BY bird_name
SELECT bird_name, location_lat, location_long, timestamp FROM BirdMigrationLocations WHERE bird_name = 'Eagle'
SELECT * FROM birds;
SELECT bird_name, location_name FROM birds;
SELECT * FROM birds WHERE location_name = 'Forest';
SELECT bird_name, migration_date FROM birds ORDER BY bird_name DESC;
SELECT bird_name, location_name FROM birds WHERE migration_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM birds WHERE location_name = 'Forest' AND bird_name LIKE 'Blue%' ORDER BY migration_date DESC;
SELECT bird_name, location_name, migration_date FROM birds WHERE migration_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT bird_id, bird_name FROM birds WHERE migration_date >= '2022-06-01' ORDER BY migration_date ASC, location_name DESC;
SELECT bird_name, latitude, longitude FROM birds INNER JOIN locations ON birds.location_name = locations.location_name WHERE birds.migration_date < '2022-08-01';
SELECT location_name, COUNT(*) AS bird_count FROM birds GROUP BY location_name HAVING COUNT(*) > 2 ORDER BY bird_count DESC, location_name ASC;
SELECT * FROM BirdLocations;
SELECT location, timestamp FROM BirdLocations ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT DISTINCT location FROM BirdLocations;
SELECT species_name, average_wingspan FROM BirdSpecies WHERE average_wingspan > 3.0;
SELECT bird_id, start_location, end_location, distance_km FROM MigrationRoutes WHERE distance_km BETWEEN 100 AND 500 ORDER BY distance_km ASC;
SELECT * FROM BirdLocations WHERE bird_id = 1;
SELECT location, timestamp FROM BirdLocations WHERE location LIKE '%forest%';
SELECT species_name, average_wingspan FROM BirdSpecies WHERE average_wingspan > 3.5;
SELECT * FROM MigrationRoutes WHERE distance_km < 1000 ORDER BY distance_km DESC;
SELECT bird_id, start_location, end_location FROM MigrationRoutes WHERE start_location <> end_location;
SELECT * FROM Birds;
SELECT bird_name, migration_date FROM Birds WHERE location_lat > 0;
SELECT bird_id, bird_name, migration_date FROM Birds ORDER BY migration_date DESC;
SELECT DISTINCT location_lat, location_long FROM Birds WHERE bird_name = 'Eagle';
SELECT watcher_id, watcher_name FROM BirdWatchers WHERE region = 'North America';
SELECT bird_name, migration_date FROM Birds;
SELECT * FROM Birds WHERE location_lat > 40 AND location_long < -100;
SELECT bird_id, species_name FROM Birds JOIN BirdSpecies ON Birds.bird_id = BirdSpecies.species_id;
SELECT watcher_name, region FROM BirdWatchers WHERE region = 'North America';
SELECT bird_id, track_date FROM BirdTracks ORDER BY track_date DESC;
SELECT * FROM bird_species;
SELECT species_name, species_id FROM bird_species ORDER BY species_name DESC;
SELECT * FROM bird_locations WHERE latitude > 40;
SELECT route_id, start_location_id, end_location_id, migration_distance FROM migration_routes WHERE migration_distance > 100;
SELECT tracking_id, bird_id, device_id, location_id, timestamp FROM bird_tracking ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT * FROM bird_species ORDER BY species_name DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT species_name, COUNT(*) AS total_count FROM bird_species GROUP BY species_name HAVING total_count > 1;
SELECT b.species_name, bl.timestamp, bl.latitude, bl.longitude FROM bird_species b INNER JOIN bird_locations bl ON b.species_id = bl.species_id ORDER BY bl.timestamp ASC;
SELECT tr.device_id, td.device_name, COUNT(*) AS total_count FROM tracking_devices td INNER JOIN bird_tracking tr ON td.device_id = tr.device_id GROUP BY tr.device_id, td.device_name;

SELECT bs.species_name, br.route_id, bl.latitude AS start_latitude, bl.longitude AS start_longitude, bl.timestamp AS start_timestamp, br.migration_distance FROM bird_species bs INNER JOIN bird_locations bl ON bs.species_id = bl.species_id INNER JOIN migration_routes br ON bl.location_id = br.start_location_id;
